我完全没打算让他当国务卿
I have no intention of offering him Secretary of State.

339
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:35,540
那么你就像沃克骗你一样骗了他
Oh, so you lied to him the way Walker lied to you.

340
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:38,580
不  我和沃克又不是老交情
No. Walker and I didn't have a history.

341
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:40,780
沃克也不尊重我
And Walker didn't respect me.

342
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:44,410
你我是有交情的  凯茜  我也非常尊重你
You and I have a history, Cathy, and I respect you immensely.

343
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:47,220
但是我们共事才3年
But our history goes back three years.

344
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:50,050
克莱尔和我已经是30年的搭档了
Claire's and my partnership goes back 30.

345
00:17:50,060 --> 00:17:51,700
你必须尊重这一点
You have to respect that.

346
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,060
我可能会...
I might have...

347
00:17:53,830 --> 00:17:56,270
如果你一开始就对我说实话的话
if you had been honest with me from the beginning.

348
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:59,510
我也希望时间能倒退  可现在已经这样了
Well, I wish I could turn back time, but here we are.

349
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,880
你可以把我挡在亚特兰大之外  想多久多久
And you can keep me out of Atlanta for as long as you want,

350
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,280
但你不能永远拖着选票
but you can't hold the vote back forever.

351
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:08,440
时间在前进不是倒退  而时间站在我这边
Time's moving forward, not back. And time is on my side.

352
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:16,540
如果希瑟·邓巴想占总统不在的便宜
If Heather Dunbar wants to take advantage of the President's absence,

353
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:17,800
那是她的权利
that's her prerogative.

354
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,250
但是她仍在华府  也未发表公开声明
But she's still in D.C., there's no public statement.

355
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:22,370
你认为这是占便宜
You see that as taking advantage?

356
00:18:22,430 --> 00:18:25,190
你认为如果不是她在华府幕后操纵
You think Congresswoman Sharp would make calls on her behalf

357
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:27,310
夏普议员会代表她打电话拉票吗
if she wasn't pulling the strings from Washington?

358
00:18:27,310 --> 00:18:29,330
夏普说是她自己打的
Sharp says she's doing it on her own.

359
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:31,830
你没有任何证据表明她们有合作
You don't have any proof of coordination.

360
00:18:31,830 --> 00:18:33,390
你说得对  我没有
You're right, I don't.

361
00:18:33,690 --> 00:18:35,510
只是清楚人性  基本逻辑
Just human nature, basic logic,

362
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:37,250
而且比常人更了解
and a slightly better than average understanding

363
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:38,990
政治手腕
of political gamesmanship.

364
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:43,670
失陪一下  新闻发言人也要上厕所
Uh, if you will excuse me, even press secretaries have to pee.

365
00:18:43,670 --> 00:18:44,830
-我马上回来  -好的
- I'll just be right back. - Okay.

366
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:46,980
失陪  抱歉  失陪
Excuse me. Excuse me. I'm sorry. Excuse me.

367
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:52,600
怎么了
What's up?

368
00:18:53,970 --> 00:18:57,060
莉安知道了  我认为是你告诉了她
LeAnn knows, and I think you told her.

369
00:18:57,060 --> 00:18:59,880
对  直截了当  我全告诉她了
I did. Straight up. I told her everything.

370
00:19:00,070 --> 00:19:02,050
-走  上楼去  -不
- Let's go. Upstairs. - No.

371
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:06,100
-你说什么  -邓巴重回局内
- Excuse me? - You've got Dunbar in play,

372
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:07,630
杜兰特和总统在一起
you got Durant with the President,

373
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:09,310
第一夫人在达拉斯
and the First Lady's in Dallas.

374
00:19:09,310 --> 00:19:10,430
这里的一屋子记者
And I've got a room full of press

375
00:19:10,430 --> 00:19:11,980
我从早上八点就在努力应付他们
that I've been keeping at bay since 8:00 this morning,

376
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:14,480
等我把熊孩子都哄睡了
so I will tell you why I told her...

377
00:19:14,910 --> 00:19:17,260
再跟你讲我为什么告诉她吧
after I tuck in all the children.

378
00:19:45,260 --> 00:19:51,980
现在投票
Let's vote now!

379
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:53,500
请安静一下
Order, please!

380
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:57,750
现在请希尔参议员讲话
It is Senator Sheer's time to speak.

381
00:19:58,830 --> 00:19:59,770
安静
Order!

382
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:02,980
也许我们应该遂凯茜的愿
Maybe we should let Cathy have her way.

383
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:07,550
如果现在投票  你们获胜  我们大选再战
If the vote's held now, you two win. We focus on the general.

384
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,250
为什么这么说
What's brought all this on?

385
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:14,690
我只是在想我们这么做
I just wonder if we're in over our heads,

386
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:16,410
是不是不自量力  弗兰西斯
Francis, trying to do this.

387
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:18,740
是因为你母亲吗
Is it your mother?

388
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:21,020
看到她病得这么重一定很不好受吧
I'm sure it's difficult to see her this sick.

389
00:20:24,530 --> 00:20:26,490
她完全无助
She's completely helpless.

390
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:30,190
但我们并不无助  我们可以扭转局势
But we're not helpless. We can turn this around.

391
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:33,980
我想我只是...
I guess I'm just...

392
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:39,590
我不知道  也许我们做错了
I don't know, maybe... maybe we're making a mistake.

393
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:42,030
也许我还没准备好做你的竞选搭档
Maybe I'm not ready to be your running mate.

394
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:46,400
-康威有个四星将军  -你母亲快乐吗
- Conway has a four-star general. - Is she happy, your mother?

395
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,190
不  她很痛苦
No, she's miserable.

396
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,280
汤姆逗她笑  但大多数时候不快乐
Tom makes her laugh, but mostly, no.

397
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:56,770
想象一下我肝衰竭了
Imagine my liver's failing.

398
00:20:56,770 --> 00:20:59,080
-想象我要死了  -弗兰西斯
- Imagine I'm dying. - Francis...

399
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,770
不  你就想象一下
No, I just want you to picture it for just a moment.

400
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:05,950
我躺在床上  像你母亲现在一样
There I am, lying in a bed just like your mother is now.

401
00:21:07,130 --> 00:21:09,560
唯一能让我高兴的事
The only thing that would make me happy

402
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:12,850
就是知道我走了以后  你会接手
is to know that you would take over after I passed.

403
00:21:13,650 --> 00:21:14,970
如果是凯茜
If it were Cathy...

404
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:18,200
我会和你母亲一样痛苦的
I'd be just as miserable as your mother is.

405
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,420
我会做好我的事
I'll do my part.

406
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:25,510
你就专注你的讲话
You just concentrate on that speech.

407
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:29,750
好  谢谢你  弗兰西斯
All right. Thank you, Francis.

408
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:30,670
晚安
Good night.

409
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:35,710
-她不吃东西吗  -她吞咽很困难
- She, uh... she won't eat? - It's hard for her to swallow.

410
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:39,940
你觉得她还有多少时间
How much time do you think she has?

411
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:46,420
我说不准  可能是几周
I can't be definitive, but... a couple of weeks, maybe.

412
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:50,000
如果她完全不进食  可能就只有几天了
If she stops eating altogether, it could be days.

413
00:21:51,270 --> 00:21:52,770
她很痛苦
She's in a lot of pain.

414
00:21:55,030 --> 00:21:56,740
她可以不用这么痛苦
She doesn't have to be.

415
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:59,910
到了这一步  我们可以让她舒适一些
When it gets to this point, we can make her comfortable.

416
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:05,420
舒适到让她的身体不再挣扎
Comfortable enough that the body will let go.

417
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,270
那是她想要的吗
Does she want that?

418
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:18,070
这个你该和你母亲讨论一下
That is something you should discuss with your mother.

419
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:23,970
我喜欢那些植物
I like the plants.

420
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,380
你放在那儿的那些
The plants you put in there.

421
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:32,530
小东西总能让人眼前一亮  对吧
It's the little things, right?

422
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:36,790
如果我们干掉精炼厂
If we take out the refineries,

423
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:38,490
就能切断他们的收入来源
that would eliminate their revenue stream.

424
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:40,920
没有了资源  他们就无法进军
They can't advance if they don't have the resources.

425
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:43,140
马克宗总统明确表示
President Makhzun made it very clear

426
00:22:43,140 --> 00:22:44,880
不希望精炼厂被毁
he wants those to remain intact.

427
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:47,360
从战略角度看  那是我们最好的选择
It's our best option from a strategic point of view.

428
00:22:47,370 --> 00:22:50,280
伤亡最小  对他们能力的冲击最大
Minimal loss of life, maximal impact on capability.

429
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:53,010
要么全面开战  要么就不打
It's either total war or nothing at all.

430
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:57,410
这可不符合外交策略  凯茜
Well, that doesn't sound very diplomatic, Cathy.

431
00:22:57,410 --> 00:22:59,640
我们要和恐怖分子谈外交吗
We're going to be diplomatic with terrorists?

432
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:01,820
我向马克宗总统承诺过
I made a promise to President Makhzun.

433
00:23:01,820 --> 00:23:04,930
你之前就违背过诺言  这次有什么不同
You've broken promises before. Why should this be any different?

434
00:23:07,590 --> 00:23:10,160
不如我们休息一下  晚餐之后继续吧
Why don't we break for dinner? We'll pick this up afterwards.

435
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,420
我想再考虑一下
I wanna review this a bit more.

436
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:13,290
我会让人把食物送去罗斯福室
I'll have some food brought into the Roosevelt Room.

437
00:23:13,290 --> 00:23:14,930
感谢各位
Thank you all very much.

438
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,280
凯茜  我们俩就在这里吃吧
Cathy, why don't you and I eat in here?

439
00:23:37,570 --> 00:23:40,330
"要么全面开战  要么就不打"
"Total war or nothing at all"?

440
00:23:41,190 --> 00:23:43,080
如果我在镜头前说
The moment I get in front of those cameras

441
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:46,870
康威是对的  布洛哈特也是对的
and I tell them that Conway is right and Brockhart is right,

442
00:23:46,870 --> 00:23:50,390
你把哈里发国的事完全搞砸了
and that you completely bungled the ICO situation,

443
00:23:50,390 --> 00:23:52,510
你觉得邓巴到时会怎么样
how do you think Dunbar will do then?

444
00:23:57,810 --> 00:24:00,270
请送两份科布沙拉过来  谢谢
Can we get two Cobb salads in here, please?

445
00:24:01,230 --> 00:24:04,490
-我不喜欢科布沙拉  -那你可以不吃
- I don't like Cobb salad. - Then you don't have to eat it.

446
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:10,980
谢谢你过来
Thanks for coming over.

447
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:13,040
我过来比你过去容易多了
Way easier coming here than you coming there.

448
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:16,000
我门外有十支新闻团队守着呢
Must be ten news crews outside of my house.

449
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,130
你怎么跑出来的
How'd you escape?

450
00:24:17,130 --> 00:24:18,990
老办法  走后门
The old-fashioned way. Back door.

451
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:20,800
你怎么弄到我的住宅电话的
How did you get my home phone?

452
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,170
老办法
Oh, old-fashioned way.

453
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:23,540
《先驱报》的联络簿
Rolodex from the Herald.

454
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:27,170
-跟我来  不会很久的  -好
- Come with me. I won't keep you long. - Yeah.

455
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:31,240
-这些花了你多少时间  -几个月
- How long did this take you? - Couple of months.

456
00:24:31,610 --> 00:24:32,830
我单独做的
I've been working on my own.

457
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,180
我们有一整队人手  都没发现这个
We had a whole team and we didn't find this.

458
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:38,250
你们或许没有深挖到贝茨城葡萄园
Well, you probably weren't digging as deep as the Bates City Vine.

459
00:24:39,620 --> 00:24:40,480
没有
No.

460
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,390
我们把大部分精力放在追踪资金上了
We spent most of our energy tracking the money.

461
00:24:43,390 --> 00:24:45,730
我们应该更关注出行记录的
We should've been more focused on the travel logs.

462
00:24:45,730 --> 00:24:48,240
我是和一个披萨店的人聊了之后才想到的
I wouldn't have checked either until I spoke with a pizza guy.

463
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:50,350
后来我想到  他们有可能篡改出行记录
Then I realized they might be manipulating the logs.

464
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:52,230
于是你查到了拉尼根
Which gets you to Lanagin.

465
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:54,460
这还是不能证明他见了拉尼根
It still doesn't prove he met with Lanagin,

466
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:56,950
但我不知道车队还能去哪
but I don't know where else that motorcade would've been heading.

467
00:24:57,170 --> 00:24:58,780
你打算把这个公开吗
Are you going public with this?

468
00:24:59,220 --> 00:25:01,900
我是可以  但是他还能合理推诿
I could, but he has some plausible deniability.

469
00:25:02,250 --> 00:25:04,310
全都推到密查姆身上
He pins it all on Meechum.

470
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:05,680
如果他掩盖了行踪
If he's covering up travel,

471
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,730
谁知道他还掩盖了什么
who knows what else he's covering up?

472
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:09,700
那才是我想要的报道
That's the story I want,

473
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:12,470
而不是什么特勤局人员修改记录
not some Secret Service man being loose with the books.

474
00:25:13,340 --> 00:25:15,120
那你还没有引起注意
So you're still under the radar.

475
00:25:19,450 --> 00:25:21,570
我得请你对这一切保密
I have to ask you to keep all this to yourself.

476
00:25:22,110 --> 00:25:25,070
我知道你现在有了机会  这很诱人
I know it can be tempting now that... you have a chance,

477
00:25:25,070 --> 00:25:28,020
但如果这一切过早公布  他会提高警惕
but if this goes public too early, his guard goes up.

478
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:31,850
我退出选举的时候很艰难
Listen, it was hard when I withdrew.

479
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:34,580
半数领导层和公众都抛弃了我
How the leadership abandoned me, how the public did.

480
00:25:34,940 --> 00:25:35,980
花了些时间
It took some time...

481
00:25:37,490 --> 00:25:38,920
但我看开了
but I made my peace.

482
00:25:39,250 --> 00:25:41,350
我是赢是输本来就不好说
It's a crapshoot whether I can win this.

483
00:25:41,350 --> 00:25:43,070
他可以反驳这样的报道
He can probably fight that off.

484
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:50,240
你得写一篇他无法反驳的报道
You need to write the story that he can't fight off.

485
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:57,160
你调查过他  突破点在哪里
You investigated him. Where's the weak link?

486
00:25:58,850 --> 00:26:00,070
雷米·丹顿
Remy Danton.

487
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,750
那是汤姆弄的
Tom did that.

488
00:26:28,850 --> 00:26:32,180
真遗憾  他会合适你的
It's a shame. He'd be good for you.

489
00:26:36,470 --> 00:26:38,420
我从没相信过牙仙
I never believed in the tooth fairy.

490
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:42,720
但你还是把钱拿走了
Well, you took the money anyway.

491
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:48,040
能帮我把那盏灯关了吗  很刺眼
Could you turn off that light, please? Hurts my eyes.

492
00:26:55,980 --> 00:26:59,720
你小时候  曾经
When you were small... you used to...

493
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:04,600
曾经求我  让黑暗停止
used to ask me to make it stop, the dark.

494
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:05,700
你还记得吗
Do you remember?

495
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:08,630
记得
Yes.

496
00:27:09,630 --> 00:27:13,160
我向你保证我会的  早上就让它停
And I promised you I would... in the morning.

497
00:27:16,430 --> 00:27:19,380
但该死的  你会每天晚上
But, damn it, you would sit at that window...

498
00:27:20,970 --> 00:27:22,050
坐在窗前
every night...

499
00:27:23,330 --> 00:27:26,870
想凭自己的力量让太阳升起来
trying to make the sun rise, all by yourself.

500
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:32,470
你脸靠在窗户上睡着后
Your daddy would put you in bed...

501
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:38,170
你爸爸会把你抱上床
after you'd fallen asleep with your face against the glass.

502
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:43,110
我那时非常嫉妒
And I was so jealous.

503
00:27:44,570 --> 00:27:45,910
嫉妒我和爸爸吗
Of me and Daddy?

504
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:49,850
嫉妒你相信
That you believed.

505
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:54,950
你相信你可以让太阳升起
You believed you could make the sun rise.

506
00:27:59,910 --> 00:28:02,260
我跟护士谈了  母亲
I spoke to her, Mother, the nurse.

507
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:07,940
我做不到
I can't do it.

508
