685
00:49:04,370 --> 00:49:06,910
在父母离世前有这样的机会
people always get before a parent dies,

686
00:49:06,910 --> 00:49:09,110
我很感激有这样的机会
and I'm grateful to have had that.

687
00:49:12,430 --> 00:49:13,990
那我在这里做什么呢
And what am I doing here?

688
00:49:18,620 --> 00:49:22,700
我站在这里  是因为这是我母亲所希望的
I'm here because my mother wanted me to be.

689
00:49:24,680 --> 00:49:26,860
昨天在她去世之前  她对我说
Yesterday, before she passed, she said to me,

690
00:49:26,870 --> 00:49:29,710
"克莱尔...去做吧
"Claire... do this.

691
00:49:30,460 --> 00:49:33,860
如果这是人们希望的  听他们的
If the people want it, listen to them.

692
00:49:34,680 --> 00:49:36,690
如果失败了  那就是失败了
And if you lose, then you lose.

693
00:49:37,620 --> 00:49:38,970
但是如果你赢了...
But if you win...

694
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:46,160
要感到荣幸  保持谦逊
be honored, be humbled,

695
00:49:46,160 --> 00:49:48,750
和弗兰西斯一起赢得选举"
and win this election with Francis!"

696
00:49:57,520 --> 00:50:00,030
我告诉她  康威夫妇是非常厉害的对手
And I told her, I said, "The Conways are tough opponents."

697
00:50:00,040 --> 00:50:03,780
她说也许是吧  但也不比德州人
And she said, "They may be tough, but they're not Texas tough."

698
00:50:08,470 --> 00:50:11,340
失去让我们深思
Loss is a sobering phenomenon.

699
00:50:11,990 --> 00:50:14,870
几个月前  我差点失去了我丈夫
Several months ago, I almost lost my husband.

700
00:50:15,260 --> 00:50:18,160
我们的国家差点失去了总统
Our nation almost lost a President.

701
00:50:20,030 --> 00:50:23,440
失去让我们重新审视我们珍惜的一切
Loss makes us reevaluate what we hold dear.

702
00:50:24,950 --> 00:50:26,740
我还要告诉你们...
And I'll tell you, there were...

703
00:50:28,010 --> 00:50:30,130
就在不久之前
times in the not too distant past,

704
00:50:30,130 --> 00:50:35,120
弗兰西斯和我...差点失去我们的婚姻
where Francis and I, we... almost lost our marriage.

705
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:39,390
我们遇到了困难  还以为坚持不下去了
Hard times when we thought we wouldn't make it.

706
00:50:40,590 --> 00:50:41,800
正如很多人所知
And like many of you know,

707
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:44,400
婚姻并非总是一帆风顺
marriage isn't always the smoothest road.

708
00:50:45,550 --> 00:50:48,920
是一个精神错乱的年轻人
And it took the actions of a deranged young man

709
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:52,660
让我记起弗兰西斯对我有多重要
to remind me how important Francis is to me.

710
00:50:54,810 --> 00:50:58,090
现在  我母亲去世了...
And now, with my mother gone...

711
00:51:01,280 --> 00:51:03,770
他就是我唯一的亲人了
he's the only family I have left.

712
00:51:04,940 --> 00:51:09,150
我愿把我的人生  我们的国家和未来
I trust Francis Underwood with my life,

713
00:51:09,520 --> 00:51:12,910
托付给弗兰西斯·安德伍德
with our nation, with our future.

714
00:51:13,670 --> 00:51:15,570
我希望你们也能信任他
I hope you will, too.

715
00:51:21,060 --> 00:51:25,150
如果你们信任我们  我会谨遵母亲的话
And if you trust the both of us, I'll heed my mother's words,

716
00:51:25,150 --> 00:51:28,970
如被提名为他的竞选搭档  我将深感荣幸
and I'll be honored if you nominate me as his running mate.

717
00:51:39,770 --> 00:51:51,280
克莱尔  克莱尔  克莱尔
Claire! Claire! Claire!

718
00:51:51,280 --> 00:51:54,180
天呐  你真厉害
Jesus! You did great work.

719
00:52:05,330 --> 00:52:06,460
女士们先生们...
Ladies and gentlemen...

720
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:14,200
秘书长女士  作为党代会主席
Madam Secretary, as Convention Chair,

721
00:52:14,540 --> 00:52:16,150
我提议通过口头表决  对提名
I move that we make the nomination

722
00:52:16,150 --> 00:52:18,670
克莱尔·安德伍德竞选副总统
of Claire Underwood for Vice President...

723
00:52:19,090 --> 00:52:22,700
弗兰西斯·安德伍德竞选总统做出表决
and Francis Underwood for President by acclamation.

724
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:41,140
对总统和副总统的提名
Do I hear a second to vote by acclamation

725
00:52:41,140 --> 00:52:44,410
进行口头表决  是否有人附议
for the nomination of the President and the Vice President?

726
00:52:44,410 --> 00:52:46,720
-说得好  -提议通过
- Hear, hear! - So moved.

727
00:52:47,330 --> 00:52:51,280
赞成提名
All of those in favor of the nomination

728
00:52:51,280 --> 00:52:52,640
弗兰斯西·安德伍德
of Francis Underwood for

729
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:55,960
竞选美国总统的说赞成
President of the United States, say "Aye."

730
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:59,430
-赞成  -反对提名的
- Aye! - All those against.

731
00:52:59,430 --> 00:53:00,400
反对
Nay!

732
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:04,870
赞成提名克莱尔·安德伍德
All those in favor of the nomination of Claire Underwood

733
00:53:04,870 --> 00:53:08,620
竞选美国副总统的说赞成
for our Vice President of the United States, say "Aye."

734
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:10,130
赞成
Aye!

735
00:53:10,590 --> 00:53:12,930
-反对提名的  -反对
- Against? - Nay!

736
00:53:13,170 --> 00:53:15,160
赞成者占多数
The Ayes have it!

737
00:53:21,230 --> 00:53:26,510
本党决定2016年总统选举候选人
Our party's ticket for the 2016 Presidential Election

738
00:53:26,510 --> 00:53:30,410
为弗兰西斯和克莱尔·安德伍德
will be Francis and Claire Underwood!

